description:
Removing one machine deletes its local pairing record and revokes the pairing on the relay (FND-2), while keeping the phone's shared device keys intact for the remaining pairings. Only when removing the LAST pairing may shared keys optionally be cleaned up.

FILES / ANCHORS:
- ios/FlightDeckRemote/Features/Settings/SettingsUnpairService.swift - today calls deletePairingRecord() AND destroys the shared key-agreement keypair. Change to target a specific pairingId and:
  1) send the phone->relay revoke (FND-2) via that instance's client;
  2) delete only that pairing's Keychain record (IOS-1) and its PairedInstance (IOS-2);
  3) stop/dispose that instance's TransportClient (IOS-3);
  4) deregister its push token (IOS-8);
  5) DO NOT destroy shared DeviceIdentity (Secure Enclave) / KeyAgreement keys unless this was the last pairing.
- UI: an unpair action in the machine's settings/detail.
